page.title: 18LIST OF WILD FLOWERS
page.content: {Flowers the children brought in were:} black medick, nipplewort, smooth sow thistle, meadow vetchling, meadow sweet, goat's beard, herb Bennet, Alexanders, tormentil, rough Hawkesweed, cross-leaved bedstraw, king-cup, cowslip, yellow archangel, primrose, groundsel, dandelion, celandine, scabious, self-heal, water speedwell, bittersweet, salsify, bugle, lamb's lettuce, common vetch, ground ivy, violet, wild pansy, periwinkle, bluebell, germander speedwell, hoary cress, bladder campion, white helleborine, Solomon's seal, common star of Bethlehem, ox-eye daisy, woodruff, wild garlic, daisy, northern rockcress, wild strawberry, hedge parsley, hog-weed, jack-by-the hedge, white deadnettle, wood anenome, chickweed, shepherd's purse, goose-grass, hedge bindweed, mallow.
